Subject: [PATCH] feat: auto-check pipeline jobs for closed/expired listings
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a '🔍 Check Closed' button to the Pipeline filter bar that hits
Greenhouse and Lever public APIs to verify each job still exists.
404 responses are treated as closed and the job is marked accordingly.
LinkedIn jobs cannot be checked from the browser (CORS blocked) and are
reported as a skip count in the result summary.

- parseJobUrlForCheck / checkJobIsOpen utility functions (CORS-safe)
- doCheckOpenJobs: batches 5 concurrent checks, updates Supabase on close
- checkingJobIds state drives a per-card "checking…" pulse indicator
- Closed jobs hidden from default pipeline view (like passed), shown via
  new "Closed" status filter pill with view/restore-all footer links
- Post-run summary banner: "Checked N jobs · M closed · K LinkedIn"

https://claude.ai/code/session_01XMewouPpZJdZ81bixEZHV5
